 King Williams Town - A 40-year-old man is expected in court on Monday after he was arrested by Tactical Response Team members deployed at Maclear. The officers conducted a search operation after receiving intelligence about an unlicensed firearm in the area of Tshikitsha locality in Katkop on Friday. "On arrival at the premises, the police were shot at through the window. However, they still managed to arrest the suspect," said police spokesperson, Captain Khaya Tonjeni. "A bullet shrapnel hit one of the members. He was immediately taken to hospital where he was treated and was released soon after receiving medical care. He is already back at work." Capt Tonjeni said that a 9mm Astra firearm with live rounds of ammunition and two spent cartridges was recovered. "Upon circulation, it was established that the firearm belongs to a man from Southridge, Mthatha. "A case of attempted murder and illegal possession of firearm and ammunition was opened and is currently under investigation," he added. "The 40-year-old suspect will appear Mount Fletcher Magistrate’s Court on Monday." Eastern Cape Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Liziwe Ntshinga commended members for the sterling success and wished the injured member a speedy recovery. "The safety of our members is of prime importance.” She encouraged police officers to take care of each other and protect themselves on duty. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 